	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/06-Where to Get Computerized</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6001.html?worth+PCFN18.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN18.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/06-Where to Get Computerized</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						By Ted C. Fishman<p>The American Association of Individual Investors has been educating investors since 1978. An independent, nonprofit organization, the AAII works hard to keep its members current when it comes to computerized investing. Now AAII's Web site (http:// www.aaii.org) makes a generous sampling of its riches available to the rest of us. For those people who have yet to introduce a computer into their investment lives, the site presents a thorough, comprehensive introduction to the entire process, from tips on gearing up to evaluations of software genres -- personal finance, technical analysis, stock screening -- and individual programs. AAII's site also provides such tools as an exhaustive glossary that defines most of the terms often used to sell an investment. In the near future, the site will offer software and shareware, more articles from AAII newsletters, and a message center where investors can trade tips and post questions. With brokers, fund companies, and software vendors all in a lather to snag on-line investors, AAII is a welcome nonpartisan refuge. <p><p><p>
KEYWORDS: Technology Industry

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
