	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b>Investing Briefs</b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/05-Investing Briefs</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						May 1996 <p>Worth magazine/Investing  <p> INVESTING BRIEFS  <p> INDEX FUNDS BY COUNTRY <p>Investors who want to buy into specific countries have two new choices this spring. Deutsche Morgan Grenfell/C. J. Lawrence's Country Baskets Index Fund (800-482-3940) and World Equity Benchmark Shares, or WEBS (800-810-9327), are products that, like shares in an index fund, mimic a single foreign country's entire market. A cross between an open-end fund and a security, these instruments, which are available for about a dozen countries, will trade on U.S. exchanges. Unlike closed-end country funds, they'll carry fees of less than 1 percent and won't trade at a discount to net asset value.  <p> OLDER AND WISER <p>Who says no one can beat the indexes? Investors seeking superior long-term returns should look to two funds managed by "ageless legends," according to the mutual-fund research company Morningstar. New Yorkbased <a name="FUND:NYVTX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/NYVTX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Davis New York Venture</b></a> (800-279-0279), run by Shelby Davis, and <a name="FUND:GPAFX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/GPAFX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Guardian Park Avenue Fund</b></a> (800-221-3253), run by Charles Albers, again ranked in the top ten of all funds for long- and short-term performance in 1995. Each scored an average annual return of almost 18 percent for the past 15 years by consistently investing in out-of-favor, low-risk, high-quality stocks.  <p> FINANCIAL FOOTNOTES <p>Children aged 5 to 18 could get a head start on their investing careers. Nasdaq will award $1,000 each to 25 winners of its essay contest. The topic: "What Stock Markets Mean to America." Send entries to Investor Relations, Nasdaq Stock Market, 1735 K St.,NW, Washington, D.C., 20006...Vanguard Group, already known for its low fees, is trimming advisory fees by 18 percent for17 of its equity and fixed-income funds, including its flagship Windsor funds.... Closed-end funds that invest in the Pacific Rim (excluding Japan) did almost twice as well as open-end fundsin the region's January rally, returning 13.8 percent versus 7.4 percent.  <p>
KEYWORDS:  Mutual Funds Investing, International Investing

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

