		<title> Worth OnLine - 93/09-Hip Hops</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6001.html?worth+PCFN18.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN18.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>93/09-Hip Hops</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						 
At last, beer buffs get their own boot camp<p>By Kevin Caliendo<p>Norm Petersen, phone home. This month, and again next spring, your fellow beer fanatics from across the country will be gathering in Fort Mitchell, Kentucky, for a weekend beer camp hosted by the six-year-old Oldenberg Brewery, one of America's most acclaimed microbreweries, best known for its German-style lagers.<p>This is serious business, dedicated to those who like to talk, drink, and learn about beer. Instructors include hops-heads like Daniel Bradford, founder of the Great America Beer Festival and publisher of All About Beer magazine, and Alan Eames, described by the Yale Journal as "the world's only beer anthropologist." (Eames will speak on "Dumb Places I Have Been in Quest of Beer.") Lab work will be stressed, too, at a hands-on home brewing class in which campers can expand their skills by experimenting with Oldenberg's various malts and barleys. <p>But there's more than just work scheduled. The activities include a five-course beer-tasting lunch, followed by a three-and-a-half-hour pub crawl in nearby Cincinnati.. Campers may well be receptive to the Temperance Hour held on Sunday between beer brunch and graduation ceremonies.<p>The camp runs from September 17-19 and again in March. The weekend costs $275 per person (double-occupancy) at the three-star Drawbridge Inn, with meals and beer included. For information call 800-426-3841.<p><p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
