<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 93/08-Cost Benefit: Learn Spanish</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6015.html?worth+PCFN16.gif+Archives>
<img src="/ads/PCFN16.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b> </b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>93/08-Cost Benefit: Learn Spanish</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						 <p>By Carla Koehl<p>Whether the motivation is travel or business__or the debatably noble idea that one really ought to be bilingual__choosing how to learn a new language shouldn't be harder than actually learning it. <p>Still, the sheer number of methods for learning, say, Spanish, is enough to make anyone quit before even beginning. We've picked some of the best choices available, offered up reviews and prices, and noted proficiency levels the average student should be able to achieve. Despite all this, it should be noted that the best known methods for achieving complete fluency are still a bottle of Rioja ($5 to $50) and a flight to Costa Rica ($720 to $920 round trip from N.Y.C.).<p>LANGUAGE BOOKS<p>Mastering Spanish, Level Two, Barron's
Cost: $14.95; Time: 1 hour a day Result: Beginners who study Barron's for 6 months will be able to read and write basic Spanish phrases.<p>Spanish: A Short Course, Harper
Cost: $38.95; Time: Too long. Result: As densely written as it is dull, it manages to pack 5 years into one. Numbing but totally thorough.<p>LANGUAGE TAPES & CDs<p>Living Language: Spanish
(includes 2 tapes or CDs, dictionary, and lesson book)
Cost: $20.00/tapes, $30.00/CDs; Time: Beginners should listen to the 90-min. tapes at least twice. Result: Updated phrases and clear explanations of grammatical patterns bring these lessons out of the "Did you have a good crossing?" dark ages, and into the "How was your trip?" present.<p>Mastering Spanish, Barron's
(includes 11 CDs; companion book) 
Cost: $100; Time: Listening to 12 hours of CDs the suggested five times could take the rest of one's adult life. Result: Beginners and intermediates can go as far with these CDs as time and patience allow, achieving near-fluency. <p>PRIVATE TUTOR<p>College student, 
found through campus newspapers' classified ads. Cost: $10/hour; Time: 10 hours. Result: Beginners will learn basic grammar and phrases. Intermediates can hone conversational skills.<p>Spanish Institute, N.Y.C. Cost: $40/hour; Time: Minimum of 10 hours. Result: Intensive program gives beginners the needed skills to travel abroad. Another 20 hours will teach them to converse, read, and write fairly fluidly. <p>IMMERSION COURSES<p>Spanish Institute, N.Y.C.
Cost: $975; Time: 1 week. Result: Beginners learn conversational confidence, basic grammar. Advanced students get solid reinforcement of all language skills. <p>Harvard Summer School, Cambridge, MA
Cost: $2,350 (+$1,950 for room and board); Time: 8 weeks, intermediates only. Result: Students are expected to achieve moderate fluency in intensive course study. <p>International Homestays, Miami, FL
Cost: $6,670; time: 4 weeks. Varying time commitments available. Result: Taking 25 hours a week of instruction and living full-time in a Spanish- speaking home results in near-fluency. __Carla Koehl
 <p><p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/2pages.gif"><br>About 2 pages

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
	</tr>
